        <abstract>
            <p>Expects R. Caspary’s paper to be published soon.</p> 
<p>Reports the conclusions of another of RC’s papers on the movement of tree branches due to cold [<hi rend="italic">Bull. Congr. Int. Bot. &amp; Hortic. Lond.</hi> (1866): 98–117]</p>  
<p>and discusses a paper by H. Lecoq on the mountain flora of the Auvergne [<hi rend="italic">Proc. Bot. Congr.</hi> (1866): 158–65]. He disagrees with CD on glaciation and its effect on geographical distribution.</p> 
        </abstract>
